The paper deals with the complexity of query answering using views in a probabilistic XML setting, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of probability in the XML setting also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses algorithms and decision procedures, which are topics that fall under the data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
